SIMPLE: uncreate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uncreate
<hw>Un`cre*ate"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>create</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of existence;
to annihilate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who can <qex>uncreate</qex> thee, thou shalt know.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncreate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Uncreate
<hw>Un`cre*ate"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>create</ets>, a.]</ety> <def>Uncreated;
self-existent.</def> <rj><au>Book of Common Prayer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncreated</ent>⟦br⟧
